  m_Name: Character_lord-aldric
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Hollowfen.Data.CharacterProfileData
  _id: lord-aldric
  _characterName: Lord Aldric
  _role: Regional lord / final negotiator
  _age: Fifties
  _home: Lord Aldric's manor
  _work: Estate management, taxation, and negotiation
  _keepsake: Signet ring
  _tagline: A polished landholder who treats every future as a set of negotiable
    terms.
  _leadParagraph: Lord Aldric is educated, well-fed, and composed, dressed in dark
    wool and velvet with a signet ring always close to the business at hand.
  _backgroundParagraph: His estate's taxes and upstream interests reach Hollowfen
    long before he meets Wren, first through Voss's ledger and then through a carefully
    written offer.
  _perspectiveParagraph: Aldric believes prosperity can be arranged by ownership,
    protection, and arithmetic. His danger lies in calm certainty rather than raised
    voices.
  _kitItems: []
  _heroPortrait: {fileID: 0}
  _pullquote: A letter is not an acquaintance. Merely an opening bid.
  _displayNameId: character.lord_aldric.name
  _descriptionId: character.lord_aldric.lead
  _sortOrder: 11
  _category: 0
  _edition: 12 / LORD ALDRIC
  _previewScale: 1
  _tPosePlate: {fileID: 0}
  _characterSheet: {fileID: 0}
  _missions:
  - Act: 2
    QuestId: firstTax
    Title: Twelve Silver by Yule
    Summary: Apply estate pressure through Voss's tax demand.
  - Act: 3
    QuestId: wendlightFound
    Title: The Wend's True Course
    Summary: Enter the river story as the name behind the upstream works.
  - Act: 3
    QuestId: aldricLetter
    Title: A Sealed Letter
    Summary: Send Wren a letter through Master Voss.
  - Act: 4
    QuestId: aldricOfferRead
    Title: The Lord's Offer
    Summary: Set out terms for patronage and control of Hollowfen's trade.
  - Act: 4
    QuestId: wendSource
    Title: The Source of the Wend
    Summary: Stand behind the estate marks found at the clear-cut.
  - Act: 4
    QuestId: meetAldric
    Title: The Meeting
    Summary: Meet Wren at the manor and negotiate Hollowfen's future.
  _quotes:
  - Text: A letter is not an acquaintance. Merely an opening bid.
    Context: Opening the manor negotiation.
  - Text: I can make Hollowfen prosperous.
    Context: Stating his offer in its simplest form.
  - Text: That is rarely the first word in a negotiation.
    Context: Answering Wren's refusal.
